The National Bureau of Production Safety Supervision and Administration aims to resolve all small coal mine problems within three years.
Meanwhile accidents continue.
Measures to improve safety include shorter working hours, fire control and ventilation equipment, and a national network of safety inspectors.
Automatic gas monitors were installed in 22 gas-rich coal mines.
China fired two provincial deputy governors, prosecuted 96 officials and fired or demoted 126 more after accident investigations.
China has created a whistleblowers fund to reward citizens reporting negligence and illegal mine investors.
Mine safety remains a major challenge as coal represents 67% of China's energy resource.
